olive oil
1 packet Green beans
2 packet Asian Greens
3 clove Garlic
½ Lime
2 packet Chicken Breast
1 packet Soy Sauce Mix
2 tsp honey
1 sachet sesame seeds

• Trim and halve green beans. Roughly chop Asian greens. Thinly slice garlic. Slice lime into wedges.
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks. Season with salt and pepper.
• In a small bowl, combine soy sauce mix, a generous squeeze of lime juice, the honey and half the sesame seeds.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook green beans and Asian greens, until tender and just wilted, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic and the remaining sesame seeds and cook, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer to serving plates, season and cover to keep warm.

• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook chicken steaks until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, and add soy-lime mixture, turning chicken to coat.

TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside.

• Divide soy-lime chicken between plates with sesame green beans and Asian greens.
• Spoon over any remaining glaze from pan. Serve with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!